|sessionend2 = March 4, 1835 |previous = 22nd |next = 24th }} The 'Twenty-third
United States Congress' was a meeting of the legislative branch of the United
States federal government, consisting of the United States Senate and the United
States House of Representatives. It met in Washington, D.C. from March 4, 1833
to March 4, 1835, during the fifth and sixth years of Andrew Jackson's
presidency. The apportionment of seats in the House of Representatives was based
on the Fifth Census of the United States in 1830. The Senate had an Anti-
Jacksonian or National Republican majority, and the House had a Jacksonian or
Democratic majority.
